Functions

void schedule_mib (module_id_t module_idP, frame_t frameP, sub_frame_t subframeP)
 MIB scheduling for PBCH. This function requests the MIB from RRC and provides it to L1. More...
 
void schedule_RA (module_id_t module_idP, frame_t frameP, sub_frame_t subframe)
 First stage of Random-Access Scheduling. Loops over the ras and checks if RAR, Msg3 or its retransmission are to be scheduled in the subframe. It returns the total number of PRB used for RA SDUs. For Msg3 it retrieves the L3msg from RRC and fills the appropriate buffers. For the others it just computes the number of PRBs. Each DCI uses 3 PRBs (format 1A) for the message. More...
 
void schedule_SI (module_id_t module_idP, frame_t frameP, sub_frame_t subframeP)
 First stage of SI Scheduling. Gets a SI SDU from RRC if available and computes the MCS required to transport it as a function of the SDU length. It assumes a length less than or equal to 64 bytes (MCS 6, 3 PRBs). More...
 
void schedule_SI_MBMS (module_id_t module_idP, frame_t frameP, sub_frame_t subframeP)
 First stage of SI Scheduling. Gets a SI SDU from RRC if available and computes the MCS required to transport it as a function of the SDU length. It assumes a length less than or equal to 64 bytes (MCS 6, 3 PRBs). More...
 
int schedule_MBMS (module_id_t module_idP, uint8_t CC_id, frame_t frameP, sub_frame_t subframe)
 MBMS scheduling: Checking the position for MBSFN subframes. Create MSI, transfer MCCH from RRC to MAC, transfer MTCHs from RLC to MAC. Multiplexing MSI,MCCH&MTCHs. Return 1 if there are MBSFN data being allocated, otherwise return 0;. More...

void fill_DLSCH_dci (module_id_t module_idP, frame_t frameP, sub_frame_t subframe, int *mbsfn_flag)
 Second stage of DLSCH scheduling, after schedule_SI, schedule_RA and schedule_dlsch have been called. This routine first allocates random frequency assignments for SI and RA SDUs using distributed VRB allocations and adds the corresponding DCI SDU to the DCI buffer for PHY. It then loops over the UE specific DCIs previously allocated and fills in the remaining DCI fields related to frequency allocation. It assumes localized allocation of type 0 (DCI.rah=0). The allocation is done for tranmission modes 1,2,4. More...
 
void schedule_dlsch (module_id_t module_idP, frame_t frameP, sub_frame_t subframe, int *mbsfn_flag)
 UE specific DLSCH scheduling. Retrieves next ue to be schduled from round-robin scheduler and gets the appropriate harq_pid for the subframe from PHY. If the process is active and requires a retransmission, it schedules the retransmission with the same PRB count and MCS as the first transmission. Otherwise it consults RLC for DCCH/DTCH SDUs (status with maximum number of available PRBS), builds the MAC header (timing advance sent by default) and copies. More...

◆ fill_DLSCH_dci()

void fill_DLSCH_dci ( module_id_t  module_idP,
frame_t  frameP,
sub_frame_t  subframe,
int *  mbsfn_flag 
)

Second stage of DLSCH scheduling, after schedule_SI, schedule_RA and schedule_dlsch have been called. This routine first allocates random frequency assignments for SI and RA SDUs using distributed VRB allocations and adds the corresponding DCI SDU to the DCI buffer for PHY. It then loops over the UE specific DCIs previously allocated and fills in the remaining DCI fields related to frequency allocation. It assumes localized allocation of type 0 (DCI.rah=0). The allocation is done for tranmission modes 1,2,4.

Parameters
Mod_idInstance of eNB
frameFrame index
subframeIndex of subframe
mbsfn_flagIndicates that this subframe is for MCH/MCCH

Synchronizing rballoc with rballoc_sub

Here is the call graph for this function:

◆ find_resource_location()

void find_resource_location ( module_id_t  module_idP,
int  number_of_rbs,
int *  rballoc_mask,
int *  rb_start_result,
int *  max_rb_length_result 
)

此為uplink slice isolation的專用函式, 負責找尋未使用資源的最大連續長度, 因為在uplink的resource allocation 表示法為 first_rb+allocation length, 因此在運算的時候要去計算目前未使用的資源最大連續長度是多少, 避免排超過限制

Parameters
module_idPInstance ID of eNB
number_of_rbsrb需求量，根據slice precentage 所得的 rb 需求量
rballoc_mask這個為rb allocation mask, 這邊會提供目前已經有被allocate 的位置, 已經被allocate掉的為1, 空閒的為0
rb_start_result這個rb_start_result 是會將搜尋結果的first rb存到這裡
max_rb_length_result這個max_rb_length_result 會紀錄所搜尋到的資源長度

)

◆ schedule_dlsch()

void schedule_dlsch ( module_id_t  module_idP,
frame_t  frameP,
sub_frame_t  subframe,
int *  mbsfn_flag 
)

UE specific DLSCH scheduling. Retrieves next ue to be schduled from round-robin scheduler and gets the appropriate harq_pid for the subframe from PHY. If the process is active and requires a retransmission, it schedules the retransmission with the same PRB count and MCS as the first transmission. Otherwise it consults RLC for DCCH/DTCH SDUs (status with maximum number of available PRBS), builds the MAC header (timing advance sent by default) and copies.

Parameters
Mod_idInstance ID of eNB
frameFrame index
subframeSubframe on which to act
mbsfn_flagIndicates that MCH/MCCH is in this subframe
Here is the caller graph for this function:

◆ schedule_MBMS()

int schedule_MBMS ( module_id_t  module_idP,
uint8_t  CC_id,
frame_t  frameP,
sub_frame_t  subframe 
)

MBMS scheduling: Checking the position for MBSFN subframes. Create MSI, transfer MCCH from RRC to MAC, transfer MTCHs from RLC to MAC. Multiplexing MSI,MCCH&MTCHs. Return 1 if there are MBSFN data being allocated, otherwise return 0;.

Parameters

frameFrame index
subframeSubframe number on which to act

First stage of PCH Scheduling. Gets a PCH SDU from RRC if available and computes the MCS required to transport it as a function of the SDU length. It assumes a length less than or equal to 64 bytes (MCS 6, 3 PRBs).

◆ schedule_RA()

void schedule_RA ( module_id_t  module_idP,
frame_t  frameP,
sub_frame_t  subframeP 
)

First stage of Random-Access Scheduling. Loops over the ras and checks if RAR, Msg3 or its retransmission are to be scheduled in the subframe. It returns the total number of PRB used for RA SDUs. For Msg3 it retrieves the L3msg from RRC and fills the appropriate buffers. For the others it just computes the number of PRBs. Each DCI uses 3 PRBs (format 1A) for the message.

Parameters
Mod_idInstance ID of eNB
frameFrame index
subframeSubframe number on which to act
